kpi_info.title: period_duration
kpi_info.use: Duration of the measurement period in minutes.

kpi_info.title: utran_not_able_exec_hho_rt
kpi_info.use: The number of intra-system hard handover failures due to UTRAN. --- The failure can occur, for example, due to the following reasons: radio resource congestion in the target cell, radio link setup/addition failure in the target BTS, relocation preparation procedure failure in the CN, or relocation resource allocation procedure failure in the target RNC. UPDATED: In Inter-RNC case: When the RNC receives an RANAP: RELOCATION PREPATION FAILURE message from the CN, or the RNC does not receive an RANAP: RELOCATION COMMAND message from the CN within a certain time period. In Intra-RNC case: When RNC internal, BTS, or transport resource reservation fails.

kpi_info.title: ue_not_able_exec_hho_rt
kpi_info.use: The number of times when during intra-system hard handover the source RNC has ordered the UE to use a configuration which the UE does not support. --- If the source RNC instructs the UE to use a configuration that it does not support, the UE will send a failure message to the source RNC. The handover procedure ends and the UE resumes normal operation as if no handover attempt had occurred."

kpi_info.title: cell_add_fail_sho_incap_rt
kpi_info.use: The number of SHO cell addition failures due to one of the following reasons: cell addition is not possible in DRNC side due to parameters, or it is not possible to reserve Iur transport resources due to congestion. This failure may lead to intra-frequency hard handover attempt."

kpi_info.title: cell_repl_fail_sho_incap_rt
kpi_info.use: The number of SHO cell replacement failures due to one of the following reasons: cell replacement is not possible in DRNC side due to parameters, or it is not possible to reserve Iur transport resources due to congestion. This failure may lead to intra-frequency hard handover attempt."

kpi_info.title: hho_att_caused_sho_incap_rt

kpi_info.title: succ_hho_caused_sho_incap_rt

kpi_info.title: unsucc_hho_csd_sho_incap_rt

kpi_info.title: FAIL_HSPA_INTRA_IFHO_UE_LOST
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Intra-RNC HSPA IFHOs due to UE being lost. UPDATED: When the UE does not respond with RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE and the user plane is released.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_HSPA_INTER_IFHO_UE_LOST
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Inter-RNC HSPA IFHOs due to UE being lost. UPDATED: When the UE does not respond with RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE and the core network does not send RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMAND.

kpi_info.title: ATT_HCAP_IFHO_MEAS
kpi_info.use: The number of HSPA capability based IFHO measurement start attempts. UPDATED: When the handover control decides to start inter-frequency measurement.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_HCAP_IFHO_MEAS
kpi_info.use: The number of HSPA capability based IFHO measurement start failures. UPDATED: When the inter-frequency measurement start command is rejected by L3 with other than an "ongoing parallel procedures" reason.

kpi_info.title: NOT_START_HCAP_IFHO_NO_CELL
kpi_info.use: The number of times when no cell good enough was found for HSPA capability based IFHO. UPDATED: When the inter-frequency measurement does not produce any handover candidate cells and the measurement is stopped.

kpi_info.title: ATT_HCAP_INTRA_IFHO
kpi_info.use: The number of Intra-RNC HSPA capability based IFHO attempts. UPDATED: When the handover control starts an intra-RNC inter-frequency handover attempt.

kpi_info.title: ATT_HCAP_INTER_IFHO
kpi_info.use: The number of Inter-RNC HSPA capability based IFHO attempts. This counter includes also handover attempts to I-HSPA cells. UPDATED: When the handover control starts an inter-RNC inter-frequency handover attempt.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_HCAP_INTRA_IFHO
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Intra-RNC HSPA capability based IFHOs. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE from the UE indicating a successful intra-RNC hard handover.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_HCAP_INTER_IFHO
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Inter-RNC HSPA capability based IFHOs. This counter includes also handovers to I-HSPA cells. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMAND from the core network indicating a successful inter-frequency handover to another RNC or I-HSPA.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_HCAP_INTRA_IFHO_UTRAN
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Intra-RNC HSPA capability based IFHOs due to UTRAN. UPDATED: When the intra-RNC inter-frequency handover fails due to some other than a UE related reason. This can be for example NBAP: RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE or Iub transmission allocation failure.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_HCAP_INTER_IFHO_UTRAN
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Inter-RNC HSPA capability based IFHOs due to UTRAN. This counter includes also failed handovers to I-HSPA cells. UPDATED: When the inter-RNC inter-frequency handover fails due to some other than a UE related reason. This can be for example RANAP: RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_HCAP_INTRA_IFHO_UE_NACK
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Intra-RNC HSPA capability based IFHOs due to UE rejection. UPDATED: When the intra-RNC inter-frequency handover fails due to UE responding with RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_HCAP_INTER_IFHO_UE_NACK
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Inter-RNC HSPA capability based IFHOs due to UE rejection. This counter includes also failed handovers to I-HSPA cells. UPDATED: When the inter-RNC inter-frequency handover fails due to UE responding with RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_HCAP_INTRA_IFHO_UE_LOST
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Intra-RNC HSPA capability based IFHOs due to UE being lost. UPDATED: When the UE does not respond to RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION sent by the RNC and the user plane is released.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_HCAP_INTER_IFHO_UE_LOST
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Inter-RNC HSPA capability based IFHOs due to UE being lost. This counter includes also failed handovers to I-HSPA cells. UPDATED: When the UE does not respond to RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION or RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION sent by the RNC and the RNC does not receive RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMAND from the core network, but a timer expires in the RNC triggering user plane release.

kpi_info.title: SCC_INTER_RNC_SUCCESS
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Inter-RNC HS-DSCH serving cell changes. Also M1008C223 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the the UE replies with RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE indicating a successful HS-DSCH serving cell change and the source and target cells are controlled by different RNCs. The counter is updated for the target cell. If the target cell is controlled by the DRNC, special object WBTS-0/WCEL-0 is used.

kpi_info.title: SCC_INTER_RNC_FAIL
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Inter-RNC HS-DSCH serving cell changes. Also one of counters M1008C217-M1008C221 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the HS-DSCH serving cell change fails and the target cell are controlled by different RNCs. The object for counter update is the old serving cell. If the cell is controlled by the DRNC, special object WBTS-0/WCEL-0 is used.

kpi_info.title: EDCH_SCC_INTER_RNC_SUCCESS
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Inter-RNC E-DCH serving cell changes. Also M1008C241 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the the UE replies with RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE indicating a successful E-DCH serving cell change and the source and target cells are controlled by different RNCs. The counter is updated for the target cell. If the target cell is controlled by the DRNC, special object WBTS-0/WCEL-0 is used.

kpi_info.title: EDCH_SCC_INTER_RNC_FAIL
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Inter-RNC E-DCH serving cell changes. UPDATED: When the E-DCH serving cell change fails and the source and target cell are controlled by different RNCs. The object for counter update is the old serving cell. If the cell is controlled by the DRNC, special object WBTS-0/WCEL-0 is used.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_IFHO_CELL_SHUTDOWN_NRT
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Inter-frequency handovers due to cell shutdown procedure for NRT. UPDATED:When the Inter-frequency handover ends. In Inter-RNC case, when an RNC receives a RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMAND message with cause "successful relocation" from

kpi_info.title: SUCC_IFHO_CELL_SHUTDOWN_RT
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Inter-frequency handovers due to cell shutdown procedure for RT. UPDATED:When the Inter-frequency handover ends. In Inter-RNC case, when an RNC receives a RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMAND message with cause "successful relocation" from t

kpi_info.title: ATT_IFHO_CELL_BLOCK_NRT
kpi_info.use: The number of Inter-frequency handover attempts due to normal priority block resource procedure for NRT. UPDATED:When the RNC decides to make an Inter-frequency hard handover attempt forced by normal priority block resource procedure. In Inter-RNC case, the RNC sends RANAP: RELOCATION REQUIRED message to a core network. In Intra-RNC case, the RNC sends RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message to the UE. This counter is updated only when the trigger reason is forced IFHO due to cell shutdown procedure for remaining UEs and for NRT.

kpi_info.title: ATT_IFHO_CELL_BLOCK_RT
kpi_info.use: The number of Inter-frequency handover attempts due to normal priority block resource procedure for RT. UPDATED:When the RNC decides to make an Inter-frequency hard handover attempt forced by normal priority block resource procedure. In Inter-RNC case, the RNC sends RANAP: RELOCATION REQUIRED message to a core network. In Intra-RNC case, the RNC sends RRC: PHYSIOCAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message to the UE. This counter is updated only when the trigger reason is forced IFHO due to normal priority block resource procedure for remaining UEs and for RT.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_IFHO_CELL_BLOCK_NRT
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Inter-frequency handovers due to normal priority block resource procedure for NRT. UPDATED:When the Inter-frequency handover ends. In Inter-RNC case, when the RNC receives RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMAND message with cause "successful relocation" from the CN. In Intra-RNC case, when an RNC receives RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from a UE. This counter is updated only when the trigger reason is forced IFHO due to normal priority block resource procedure for remaining UEs and for NRT.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_IFHO_CELL_BLOCK_RT
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Inter-frequency handovers due to normal priority block resource procedure for RT. UPDATED:When the Inter-frequency handover ends. In Inter-RNC case, when the RNC receives RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMAND message with cause "successful relocation" from the CN. In Intra-RNC case, when an RNC receives RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from a UE. This counter is updated only when the trigger reason is forced IFHO due to normal priority block resource procedure for remaining UEs and for RT

kpi_info.title: ATT_HSUPA_IFHO
kpi_info.use: "The number of HSUPA IFHO attempts. Also M1008C250 or M1008C251 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the handover control starts an inter-frequency handover attempt during HSUPA allocation and the channel type is not downgraded. The trigger is the actual handover execution start after a successful IFHO measuring has already been performed and a target cell found."

kpi_info.title: SUCC_HSUPA_IFHO
kpi_info.use: "The number of successful HSUPA IFHOs. Also M1008C252, M1008C253, M1008C254 or M1008C255 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the RNC receives a RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMAND from the core network indicating a successful inter-RNC handover or when the RNC receives an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE from the UE indicating a successful intra-RNC handover."

kpi_info.title: ATT_MBLB_IFHO_UE_BAND_CAPA
kpi_info.use: The number of Multi-Band Load Balancing (MBLB) IFHO attempts with UE band capability as highest trigger weight. UPDATED: When the handover control starts inter-frequency handover attempt due to UE band capability had highest weighting factor. If L3 rejects the handover attempt with cause "parallel procedures not allowed", the counter is not updated.

kpi_info.title: ATT_MBLB_IFHO_SERVICE_UE_CAP
kpi_info.use: The number of Multi-Band Load Balancing (MBLB) IFHO attempts with service and UE feature capability as highest weight. UPDATED: When the handover control starts inter-frequency handover attempt due to service and UE feature had highest weighting factor. If L3 rejects the handover attempt with cause "parallel procedures not allowed", the counter is not updated.

kpi_info.title: ATT_MBLB_IFHO_RSCP
kpi_info.use: The number of Multi-Band Load Balancing (MBLB) IFHO attempts with RSCP as highest trigger weight. UPDATED: When the handover control starts inter-frequency handover attempt due to RSCP had highest weighting factor. If L3 rejects the handover attempt with cause "parallel procedures not allowed", the counter is not updated.

kpi_info.title: ATT_MBLB_IFHO_LOAD
kpi_info.use: The number of Multi-Band Load Balancing (MBLB) IFHO attempts with load as highest weight. UPDATED: When the handover control starts inter-frequency handover attempt due to load had highest weighting factor. If L3 rejects the handover attempt with cause "parallel procedures not allowed", the counter is not updated.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_MBLB_IFHO
kpi_info.use: "The number of successful Multi-Band Load Balancing (MBLB) IFHOs. This is a common success counter for attempt counters M1008C296, M1008C297, M1008C298 and M1008C299. UPDATED: When the handover control gets ack from L3 that MBLB IFHO was successful."

kpi_info.title: FAIL_MBLB_IFHO_UTRAN
kpi_info.use: "The number of failed Multi-Band Load Balancing (MBLB) IFHOs due to UTRAN. This is a common failure counter for attempt counters M1008C296, M1008C297, M1008C298 and M1008C299. UPDATED: When the preparation phase for IFHO fails. It can be either SRNS resource reservation failure (intra-RNC case) or RANAP: RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE (inter-RNC case)."

kpi_info.title: FAIL_MBLB_IFHO_UE_NACK
kpi_info.use: "The number of failed Multi-Band Load Balancing (MBLB) IFHOs due to negative UE response. This is a common failure counter for attempt counters M1008C296, M1008C297, M1008C298 and M1008C299. UPDATED: When the UE responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE (or other RRC nack) and remains in the original cell in Cell_DCH state."

kpi_info.title: FAIL_MBLB_IFHO_UE_LOST
kpi_info.use: "The number of failed Multi-Band Load Balancing (MBLB) IFHOs due to UE lost. This is a common failure counter for attempt counters M1008C296, M1008C297, M1008C298 and M1008C299. UPDATED: When the UE does not respond anything to the handover command 8intra-RNC case) or CN does not send IU RELEASE COMMAND (inter-RNC case), timer expires in the RNC and the UE is dropped out from Cell_DCH state. The counter is updated also if the UE sends Cell Update.

kpi_info.title: ATT_MBLB_IFHO_FAST_UE
kpi_info.use: The number of Multi-Band Load Balancing (MBLB) IFHO attempts due to fast moving UE. UPDATED: When the handover control starts inter-frequency handover attempt due to fast moving UE.

kpi_info.title: NOT_START_MBLB_IFHO_NO_CELL
kpi_info.use: The number of times when no cell good enough was found for Multi-Band Load Balancing (MBLB) IFHO. UPDATED: When the inter-frequency measurement does not produce any handover candidate cells and the measurement is stopped.
